{{biochemistry}} a [[complex]] [[polymer]] in which [[monomer]]s (such as [[amino acid]]s, [[nucleic acid]]s, or [[sugar]]s) are [[covalent]]ly [[bond]]ed often in a [[linear]] [[chain]]. In this way, [[amino acid]]s are [[join]]ed together to make [[protein]]s; [[nucleic acid]]s form [[DNA]] or [[RNA]]; and [[sugar]]s form [[polysaccharide]]s. [[Branch]]es in the [[polymer]] [[chain]]s, though less frequent, can occur in all three types of biopolymers.